The paper deals with reinforcement learning and inverse reinforcement learning, which are subfields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The proposed method is based on Bayesian inverse reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of probabilistic machine learning. The evaluation of the proposed method involves grid navigation and simulated driving tasks, which are related to robotics and control. The paper also discusses risk-aware policy selection and improvement, which are relevant to cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
